"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-murray-evans-tennis-olympics-2024-b1173681.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport|Olympics  Andy Murraysays he andDan Evansneed to start fast and recreate the level they showed when five match points down in their opening-round match to continue their Olympic dream in Paris.  The two-time Olympic champion looked set for a limp end to his professional career when trailing 9-4 to Kei Nishikori and Taro Daniel in the deciding tiebreak of their doubles match on Sunday night.  But he and Evans produced their best tennis of the matchto seal an unlikely win and stretch his professional career into another day.  The British pair are the fourth match on Suzanne Lenglen court,expected to start from about 4pm BST on Tuesday, against Belgian duo Sander Gille and Joran Vliegen.  Murray said: \\\"At the end of the match, I was jumping around so happy but, as we were getting back, I felt pretty calm and played my best at the end. When it mattered, I raised my level and I need to try to find a way of starting the [second-round] match like that.  \\\"When it clicks for us, we have the potential to play really well together because our games complement each other really well.  \\\"Certainly from my side, I did not think I was playing well [in the opening match]. Evo played well at times but, for both of us, we can play much better than that.\\\"  Rafael Nadal issues latest retirement update after Olympics defeat by Novak Djokovic  Andy Murray's bold Olympics call vindicated amid dreams of a 'special' farewell  Both players said they had never clawed their way back from five match points before in their careers and Evans jokingly threatened to walk off court if Murray put him in that position again.  Despite it being a first-round match, Evans described it as a career highlight but said he was far from done with the Olympics.  \\\"It's something I will remember forever,\\\" he said, \\\"but it would be amazing if we could go on to do something really special this week. Let us not make it one match, let us make it another and see how we go.\\\"  If they win that, they likely face the formidable obstacle of Taylor Fritz and Tommy Paul in the quarter-finals.  Fritz was the obstacle for another British player in the singles in the opening match on the same court against British No1 Jack Draper.  Meanwhile, Emma Raducanu, who opted to miss the Olympics because of the risk to her body of going from grass to clay so abruptly, returned to winning ways in her first match since Wimbledon.  In a see-saw encounter, she saw off No8 seed Elise Mertens 6-2, 3-6, 6-4 to move into the second round of the Citi Open in Washington.  Following that win, she said: \\\"I was playing some pretty good tennis in patches throughout especially in the first set and moments in the third set.  \\\"I lost some focus in the second. It's not easy playing at 11.30. I got here Thursday night so I am still jetlagged. But I was telling myself, 'I am not leaving, this is not happening, you are not losing this match'.\\\"  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"